	abstract = {This work summarizes our current understanding of the elongation and termination/recycling phases of eukaryotic protein synthesis. We focus here on recent advances in the field. In addition to an overview of translation elongation, we discuss unique aspects of eukaryotic translation elongation including {eEF}1 recycling, {eEF}2 modification, and {eEF}3 and {eIF}5A function. Likewise, we highlight the function of the eukaryotic release factors {eRF}1 and {eRF}3 in translation termination, and the functions of {ABCE}1/Rli1, the Dom34:Hbs1 complex, and Ligatin ({eIF}2D) in ribosome recycling. Finally, we present some of the key questions in translation elongation, termination, and recycling that remain to be answered. © 2012 Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory Press; all rights reserved.},
